Yea, I got the same feeling on the Edgar episode too <@U4V5EHQ2G>. I was hearing some card choices and thinking "....why?"
It was a bad title for the episode.
The deck was still very much a command zone deck. Not really how a "spike" would put it
I think they could have titled it "how would you make Edgar 'mean'?" And it been more accurate. But CZ isn't about playing mean so they had to pin it on the spike community
I was thinking why they had a token deck with red but no purphoros or impact tremors. Because that's what a spike would actually do
One metas cutthroat spikes deck is another ones ... not that I guess
But as designed it looked to be the worst kind of configuration; a deck that makes things miserable to play against but doesn't really win

I was a little more perturbed by titles like "Can cat tribal be competitive" and "Are wizards underpowered," myself. Just that they never actually asked those questions in the episodes. Was a little click-baity. Oh well.
That is a good point though. You kinda need clickbaity titles I guess so maybe the problem was mostly me forgetting that
Wizards a little more divided, but not underpowered per se

Think I need more draw in my Edgar build. I have three small draw spells (Night's Whisper, Sign in Blood, Read the Bones) two larger ones (Ancient Craving, Ambition's Cost) plus Skull Clamp and Phyrexian Arena. I guess Yawgmoth's Will kinda counts. Necropotence at 3 black is kind of a pain in a three color deck. Outpost Siege? Wheel? Red small draw like Tormenting Voice/Magmatic Insight/Cathartic Reunion?
